cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM 

The paper deals with texture synthesis using convolutional neural networks (ConvNets) and deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the probabilistic framework of generative ConvNets, which suggests a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper explores the theoretical connections between their model and other texture models, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions texture expansion and inpainting, which could be related to cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
